POLICE have launched a manhunt after a raid on a shop in Renfrewshire. Police step up hunt for Renfrewshire robber POLICE have launched a manhunt after a raid on a shop in Renfrewshire.Staff at Hasan Stores in Broomlea Crescent, Inchinnan were forced to hand over a three-figure sum of cash during the robbery.It happened on Tuesday as workers were &quot;cashing up&quot; for the evening.Police believe the suspect, who was wearing a scarf over his face, was hanging around the shop entrance for around 15 minutes before the robbery.A spokesman said: &quot;&quot;We will be stepping up local patrols.&quot; 